¹ They appear in the two Sacramentaries under the title Praefatio hectoris, thus forming a counterpart to the invitatories employed for the other orders3 but their form is widely different. I have been inclined to place them at the beginning of the ceremony, that is, at the moment indicated by the sense of the formulary. The blessing would thus appear without an invitatory. Perhaps the address of the bishop took its place; but this is not very probable. The Pontifical now in use has a special invitatory.
